comment:
* Information returned after waiting for an activity start.
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: LAUNCH_STATE_UNKNOWN
variables.comment: * Not considered as a launch event, e.g. the activity is already on top.

variables.name: LAUNCH_STATE_COLD
variables.comment: * Cold launch sequence: a new process has started.

variables.name: LAUNCH_STATE_WARM
variables.comment: * Warm launch sequence: process reused, but activity has to be created.

variables.name: LAUNCH_STATE_HOT
variables.comment: * Hot launch sequence: process reused, activity brought-to-top.

variables.name: LAUNCH_STATE_RELAUNCH
variables.comment:
* Relaunch launch sequence: process reused, but activity has to be destroyed and created.
     * E.g. the current device configuration is different from the background activity that will be
     * brought to foreground, and the activity doesn't declare to handle the change.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(Parcel dest, int flags)
public void dump(PrintWriter pw, String prefix)
public static String launchStateToString(@LaunchState int type)
